how to continue schooling. Schooling in this county is not free, nor cheap. I am getting extremely tired of working while attending university. I am looking for people to help financially support my education. I would love to get into the journalism field, but I am aware that there are not a lot of job opportunities in Cambodia.

I would like to be granted a honorary scholarship, to be able to continue my schooling, so that I can continue my dream. Life in Cambodia is extremely hard because Cambodia is a 3rd world country where our lost and proud history has caught up with us, causing us a country with great poverty.

I would like to give back so desperately to my country. Cambodia is such a beautiful country, with so much potential. Poverty has engulfed our country in the way it never left. My dream is to go back home, work with my government on the issue of poverty, cleanliness, and how to be more responsible members of society. My dream is alway to come back to Cambodia, and help my people.

I have a really hard time explaining to those around me my drive. My life involves many hardships, yet I never feel this drive being washed away. My mother tries to understand and help in any way she can, but sometimes she is distracting and dependent on me for survival. It is a rough world, with an extremely rough life, yet I am not those things. Life is precious and amazing, but it can be hard.
